    {
      "content": "2. Utilize Existing Secondary Replica(s): Multi-Site",
      "pos": [
        34030,
        34082
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you have nodes in more than one Azure datacenter (DC) or if you have a hybrid environment, then you can use an AlwaysOn configuration in this environment to minimize downtime.",
      "pos": [
        34084,
        34262
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The approach is to change the AlwaysOn synchronization to Synchronous for the on-premises or secondary Azure DC, and then failover over to that SQL Server.",
      "pos": [
        34264,
        34419
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Then copy the VHDs to a Premium Storage account, and redeploy the machine into a new cloud service.",
      "pos": [
        34420,
        34519
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Update the listener, and then fail back.",
      "pos": [
        34520,
        34560
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Points of Downtime",
      "pos": [
        34569,
        34587
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The downtime consists of the time to failover to the alternative DC and back.",
      "pos": [
        34589,
        34666
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It also depends on your client/DNS configuration and your client reconnection may be delayed.",
      "pos": [
        34667,
        34760
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Consider the following example of a hybrid AlwaysOn configuration:",
      "pos": [
        34761,
        34827
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "![MultiSite1][9]",
      "pos": [
        34829,
        34845
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Advantages",
      "pos": [
        34853,
        34863
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can utilize existing infrastructure.",
      "pos": [
        34867,
        34907
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You have the option to pre-upgrade the Azure storage on the DR Azure DC first.",
      "pos": [
        34910,
        34988
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The DR Azure DC storage can be reconfigured.",
      "pos": [
        34991,
        35035
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There is a minimum of two failovers during migration, excluding test failovers.",
      "pos": [
        35038,
        35117
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You do not need to move SQL Server data with backup and restore.",
      "pos": [
        35120,
        35184
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Disadvantages",
      "pos": [
        35192,
        35205
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Depending on client access to SQL Server, there might be increased latency when SQL Server is running in an alternative DC to the application.",
      "pos": [
        35209,
        35351
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The copy time of VHDs to Premium storage could be long.",
      "pos": [
        35354,
        35409
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This might affect your decision on whether to keep the node in the Availability Group.",
      "pos": [
        35410,
        35496
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Consider this for when log intensive work loads are running during the migrationis required, since the Primary node will have to keep the unreplicated transactions in its transaction log.",
      "pos": [
        35497,
        35684
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Therefore this could grow significantly.",
      "pos": [
        35685,
        35725
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This scenario would use the Azure <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Start-AzureStorageBlobCopy<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> commandlet, which is asynchronous.",
      "pos": [
        35728,
        35827
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There is no SLA on completion.",
      "pos": [
        35828,
        35858
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The time of the copies varies, while this depends on wait in queue, it will also depend on the amount of data to transfer.",
      "pos": [
        35859,
        35981
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Therefore you just have one node in your 2nd data center, you should take mitigation steps in case the copy takes longer than in testing.",
      "pos": [
        35982,
        36119
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This could include the following ideas.",
      "pos": [
        36120,
        36159
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Add a temporary 2nd SQL node for HA before the migration with agreed downtime.",
      "pos": [
        36166,
        36244
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Run the migration outside of Azure scheduled maintenance.",
      "pos": [
        36251,
        36308
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Ensure you have configured your cluster quorum correctly.",
      "pos": [
        36316,
        36373
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This scenario assumes that you have documented your install and know how the storage is mapped in order to make changes for optimal disk cache settings.",
      "pos": [
        36376,
        36528
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "High Level Steps",
      "pos": [
        36536,
        36552
      ]
    },
    {
