      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Step 7: Change Failover Partners and Replication Modes",
      "pos": [
        46162,
        46216
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you have more than 2 SQL Servers, you should change the failover of another secondary in another DC or on premise to ‘Synchronous’ and make it an Automatic Failover Partner (AFP), this is so you maintain HA whilst you are making changes.",
      "pos": [
        46218,
        46458
